description: Best value play in Lakeshore East's Premier full amenity high-rise building front and center opening up to the Lakeshore East Park, Village Market with Mariano's Ming Hihn, dentist, chiropractor, vet, hair/nail salon and home to 7 restaurants. Residence 1206 features floor to ceiling windows, separate living and dining spaces that accommodate a fourth seating area great for a home office. Residence 1206 is a 1,244 square foot northwest corner home with extra large near 12 foot island, comfortable seating for 6, gas cooktop, vented culinary hood, built into cabinet oven, GE Monogram stainless steel appliance series, Flat panel Snaidero cabinetry, 1.25" quartz counters, single color, glass mosaic backsplash, under mount sink, disposal. Gallery hallway and formal entry for art, painting/photography display. Bamboo hardwood floors. Powder room. In unit washer and dryer. Primary suite with walk in and linen closets. dual Snaidero vanity, soaking tub and shower combination. Bathroom dressed in floor to ceiling natural stone. Enjoy views of the Lakeshore East Park, Pritzker Pavilion in Millennium Park and architectural wall of some of Chicago's most storied buildings on South Michigan Ave. Nearly 1250 square feet and the size of most two bedrooms in most neighborhood high-rise buildings. 340 on the Park is a full amenity building featuring 24 hour doorstaff, onsite management and maintenance staff, dry cleaners, outdoor pet relief area, short cut to Mariano's and the restaurants and services of the Village Market, 25th floor 75' two lane indoor lap pool, whirlpool, dry sauna, steam rooms, sun terrace, gas grills, patio furniture, Wintergarden, Private dining and conference room, complete caterer's kitchen, 4,000 square foot gym facility where outside trainers are welcome. Heated garage parking spaces are available from $35,000 to $40,000 on P1 and P5. Ask Listing Broker for details. Residence 1206 will not last price at $401 per square foot in the best location in Lakeshore East at the base of Chicago's largest front yard and on Lake Michigan.
